4. Side-by-side per usage_dt (easiest to compare DEV vs PROD)

SELECT 
    aep_usage_dt,
    hdp_update_user,
    COUNT(*) as cnt,
    COUNT(DISTINCT serialnumber) as dist_meters,
    SUM(CASE WHEN aep_premise_nb IS NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as null_premise,
    SUM(CASE WHEN aep_service_point IS NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as null_svc_point,
    SUM(CASE WHEN value IS NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as null_value,
    ROUND(AVG(value), 4) as avg_value,
    ROUND(SUM(value), 4) as sum_value
FROM usage_nonvee.reading_ivl_nonvee_oh
GROUP BY aep_usage_dt, hdp_update_user
ORDER BY aep_usage_dt DESC, hdp_update_user;
5. Spot-check specific meter (pick a serialnumber from DEV, run same on PROD)

-- Replace 'YOUR_SERIAL' with an actual serialnumber from your dev results
SELECT 
    serialnumber, aep_channel_id, aep_raw_uom, endtimeperiod, starttimeperiod,
    value, aep_raw_value, scalarfloat,
    aep_premise_nb, aep_service_point, aep_derived_uom,
    aep_mtr_install_ts, aep_mtr_removal_ts,
    aep_city, aep_zip, aep_state,
    hdp_update_user, hdp_insert_dttm, hdp_update_dttm,
    aep_usage_dt
FROM usage_nonvee.reading_ivl_nonvee_oh
WHERE serialnumber = 'YOUR_SERIAL'
ORDER BY endtimeperiod, aep_channel_id;
Run query 1 first on both environments to get the full column profile, then compare queries 2 & 3 for insert/update splits. Query 4 gives you the quickest row-by-row date comparison. Query 5 lets you drill down to a specific meter for exact value matching.

